Package graphsDSESIUCLM

This package provides the interfaces and classes needed to work with simple graphs.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Edge<E>
    This class represents the basic functional behavior of an edge in a graph.
    Element
    This interface defines the existence of a string used as an ID for an element to store in a vertex or an edge.
    Graph<V,E>
    This interface defines the functionality of an undirected graph where elements can be stored in vertices and edges.
    Vertex<V>
    This class represents the basic functional behavior of a vertex in a graph.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    TreeMapGraph<V,E>
    This class implements the interface Graph.

Package graphsDSESIUCLM Description
